    <h2>Why I Sketch</h2>
    <p>
      Sketching helps me slow down and observe the world more carefully. It sharpens my attention to detail—an essential skill for UX design too. Whether it’s doodling in a notebook or capturing urban scenes, sketching clears my mind and boosts creativity.
    </p>

    <h2>Materials I Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Moleskine Sketchbooks</li>
      <li>Micron pens and graphite pencils</li>
      <li>Watercolors for quick washes</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>My Favorite Subjects</h2>
    <p>
      I love drawing street scenes, people in cafés, and nature. These quick sketches capture the atmosphere and emotions of a moment.
    </p>

